refactor+feat: shared prisma schema at root + SEO for web

## Shared Prisma (task 6)
- New /prisma/ at repo root — single source of truth for
  schema.prisma + seed.ts. No more copy-paste sync between apps.
- admin/prisma/ and web/prisma/ removed (duplicates + a stale
  migrations folder in admin that was never used)
- admin/package.json prisma field: schema + seed both point to
  ../prisma/*
- web/package.json prisma field: schema at ../prisma/schema.prisma;
  postinstall hook passes --schema explicitly so it works from
  the web/ workdir
- Dockerfile (master, builds admin): COPY prisma/ /prisma/ before
  COPY admin/ . so the shared schema is at /prisma/ inside the
  container while WORKDIR /app has admin/ contents. package.json's
  ../prisma/schema.prisma resolves to /prisma/schema.prisma.

Verified: npx prisma generate + npx next build pass on both apps
using the shared schema.

## SEO (task 7)
- lib/site-url: SITE_URL from NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL env, defaults
  to fnb-webapp.vibe.matbao.net; SITE_NAME constant
- app/robots.ts: dynamic robots.txt with sitemap + host; disallows
  /api/
- app/sitemap.ts: dynamic sitemap.xml — 5 static routes
  (/, /menu, /blog, /about, /contact) plus one entry per
  PUBLISHED post, using updatedAt as lastModified. Gracefully
  returns just the static routes if the Post table is unreachable.
- Removed the old static public/robots.txt (was conflicting with
  the new dynamic route) and added .gitkeep so the public folder
  survives in git.
- Root layout: metadataBase + full openGraph + twitter card + robots
  index/follow + canonical
- /blog/[slug] generateMetadata: per-post openGraph (article type
  with publishedTime + authors), twitter card with cover image,
  canonical /blog/{slug}

Verified via dev server: /robots.txt returns "User-Agent: *\n
Allow: /\nDisallow: /api/\n...", /sitemap.xml returns valid XML
with all 5 static routes, and the home page HTML contains all
expected og:* and twitter:* meta tags.
